For any non-negative integer 
\begin_inset Formula $l$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $u$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\sum_{j=0}^{l}\sum_{k=0}^{\min(l-u,j)}x^{j-k}Q(j,k)=\sum_{v=0}^{l}x^{v}\sum_{k=0}^{l-\max(u,v)}Q(v+k,k).
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Obviously, the order 
\begin_inset Formula $v=j-k$
\end_inset

 of factor 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 can vary from 
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

 (say, when 
\begin_inset Formula $j=0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $k=0$
\end_inset

) to 
\begin_inset Formula $l$
\end_inset

 (when 
\begin_inset Formula $j=l$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $k=0$
\end_inset

).
 Therefore: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sum_{j=0}^{l}\sum_{k=0}^{\min(l-u,j)}f^{j-k}g(j,k)=\sum_{v=0}^{l}f^{v}\sum_{k\in K(l,u,v)}g(v+k,k),
\]

\end_inset

where the set 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 is defined as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
K(l,u,v) & = & \{k|0\le j\le l\wedge0\le k\le\min(l-u,j)\wedge j-k=v\}\\
 & = & \{k|k\le l-v\wedge0\le k\le\min(l-u,v+k)\}.
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
It is convenient to consider two cases separately 
\begin_inset Formula $v\le u$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $v>u$
\end_inset

.
 For the former case 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
K_{v\le u}=\{k|k\le l-v\wedge0\le k\le\min(l-u,k+v)\wedge v\le u\}.
\]

\end_inset

When 
\begin_inset Formula $v\le u$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $k\le l-v\le l-u\le\min(l-u,k+v)$
\end_inset

